						               													<description>It's the end of the Roman Empire: barbarians at the gates, rebels inside the empire, fighting in the senate.&amp;#10;Will you be able to avoid fate, or will Rome be destroyed?&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Delenda Roma is a single player board game when you try to stop the inevitability of the history.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;At the start of the game player get a limited amount of gold and armies to be placed on roman provinces, then gameplay is divided in phases:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     Event phase: from a deck of cards a new challenge is revealed ( like for example new barbarian invading from outside of the empire or a rebellion on the roman provinces).&amp;#10;     Battle phase: for provinces with enemy armies a deterministic fight occurs&amp;#10;     Upkeep phase: determine for provinces who is in control and apply consequences&amp;#10;     Enemy phase: every enemy units move according to their type&amp;#10;     Player phase: player can spend gold to move armies (by land and sea), recruit new armies, placate rebels or bribe the senate&amp;#10;     Senate phase: from another deck of cards a senate card is revealed and player has limited turns to fulfil the mission&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Player lose when barbarian or rebels take control of Roma and win if they can survive at least 20 turns.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the designer&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
